The paper deals with the development of an intelligent interface for detecting mind wandering using EEG signals. This involves the use of deep learning models, specifically a channel-wise deep convolutional neural network (CNN) model. The paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category as it deals with the development of an intelligent interface. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves the use of deep learning models. Additionally, the paper may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of EEG signals. It may also belong to the Computational Biology (cs.CB) sub-category as the study of mind wandering has implications for cognitive neuroscience. Finally, the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it involves the development of an intelligent system for detecting mind wandering.
